one, but it is not a requirement. I have probably asked 40 different clerics for rezz's at one time or another. I do the /who cleric thing, and check zones. trying to get someone as close as possible, if they are more than one zone away, I don't even bother them. Then I send personal, respectful tells. I have never gotten a rude response, and I have always accepted declines with grace, thank them for their time. I can respect that someone is busy. I don't spend all day hanging out doing nothing, why should they? I have actually gotten clerics to come in from another zone to rezz someone, and I showed my gratitude, thanked them for their time, made sure they were compensated. As a Shaman, I rarely have time to run across a zone to buff someone, much less go to another zone to do it. I would expect no more of a cleric. There are a lot of wonderful people that are clerics, who help us in so many ways. We shouldn't take advantage, and we should respect their right to play when they want, and how they want. And as for those people who don't use their head when asking for someones time, it's their loss, and they only serve to make me look better when I ask. Keep it up! lol<br>
<br>
Whytspirit Mystreaver<br>
